        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         \xe2\x80\x9cWhile we\xe2\x80\x99re building infrastructure,\xe2\x80\x9d Uri said, \xe2\x80\x9cWe have to remember that it\xe2\x80\x99s the products we offer that will actually drive demand.\xe2\x80\x9d Things like:
        </p>
        <ul style="margin-top: 0; padding: 0;">
         <li style="margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">
           Better access to capital and financing
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">
           Better stock loan to borrow
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">
           More margin, cross margining and enhanced leverage
          </p>
         </li>
         <li style="margin: 8px 0 0 32px; mso-special-format: bullet;">
          <p style="box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;">
           \xe2\x80\x9cProducts \xe2\x80\x93 more and more integrated products\xe2\x80\x9d
          </p>
         </li>
        </ul>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         As one example of the products modern infrastructure can support, Clear Street can build products on its single source of truth, real-time data that take advantage of pre-trade analytics, predictive risk modeling, and intelligence instead of reactive products that wait for the data to catch up.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Studio has a \xe2\x80\x9cShocks View\xe2\x80\x9d that lets clients see what would happen to their portfolio and margin requirements if asset prices swung violently up or down. It also has built-in risk simulations that let clients ask \xe2\x80\x9cWhat would happen if I put this trade on?\xe2\x80\x9d both to the existing portfolio and in the case of shocks. Currently, to do this, traders pick up the phone and ask their risk team what the impact might be. In a field in which milliseconds can make a difference, the speed advantage from replacing phone calls with software can be enormous.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         As another, moving everything onto one real-time cloud software platform means that Clear Street can provide more bespoke margin, lending, and financing packages that respond in real-time to clients\xe2\x80\x99 portfolios.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Because Clear Street is building API-first, third parties can build products that inherit these advantages on top of its infrastructure and/or Clear Street can offer those products itself.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         For now, many of those products are assets. Clear Street started by offering just US equities. Then it added options, fixed income, and swaps. Now, it\xe2\x80\x99s scaling out the swaps business and building a futures business.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         <span>
          In July,
         </span>
         <a href="https://substack.com/redirect/02b1fa32-db92-4493-a6bb-cad53418042d?j=eyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8ExkRNpU" rel="" style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">
          it acquired React
         </a>
         <span>
          , the maker of cloud-native futures clearing platform BASIS, and it recently applied for Futures Commission Merchant (FCM) membership. It\xe2\x80\x99s the kind of acquisition a company can make when it\xe2\x80\x99s well-capitalized enough to be acquisitive but small and technologically clean enough to integrate new products smoothly.
         </span>
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Then, it needs to bring those products to major markets around the globe, each of which has its own regulations and its own antiquated systems with which to integrate. My head hurts.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Oh, and it launched an investment banking business.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Andy Volz, Clear Street\xe2\x80\x99s COO and Head of Prime Sales, is responsible for bringing in hedge fund clients. And he said that a big part of that \xe2\x80\x93 of getting hedge funds and other institutional clients to try and trust the technology Clear Street has built in the first place \xe2\x80\x93 is offering them the services that investment banks offer.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         \xe2\x80\x9cThese are discerning customers, and it\xe2\x80\x99s hard to get them to trust you,\xe2\x80\x9d Andy said. \xe2\x80\x9cClients traditionally come in in one of a few ways: research, corporate access, capital introductions, balance sheet. We didn\xe2\x80\x99t have that stuff, and now we do.\xe2\x80\x9d
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         And even with all of that stuff, winning prime brokerage clients still requires a sales team with the right relationships. Some know a few big clients really well, others cover 200 smaller clients. Clear Street started with that group, targeting the hedge funds that the big banks don\xe2\x80\x99t focus on.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         With Studio, a self-serve product, they can open up the top-of-funnel even further to capture the long-tail of the roughly 6,000-8,000 hedge funds in their addressable market.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Software, services, and sales. Winning a foothold in prime brokerage requires all three. And from that foothold, Clear Street can expand its share of wallet as it adds new products in new geographies that those same clients, and new ones, want to use.
        </p>
        <p style="color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;">
         Eventually, the goal is to serve all types of clients \xe2\x80\x93 from the day-trader to the largest multi-strategy hedge funds like Alpine \xe2\x80\x93 across all of their needs. It\xe2\x80\x99s better for Clear Street, obviously, but they believe that it\xe2\x80\x99s also better for those clients from a risk, financing, and speed perspective.
        </p>
        <div class="captioned-image-container-static" style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 32px auto;">
         <figure style="margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;">
          <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" class="image-wrapper" data-component-name="Image2ToDOMStatic" style="mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;" width="100%">
